   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC06ba5f502e4d10058389c272b5ad609c"></a>Resetting the Throttle Potentiometer Sensor (TPS)
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4123"> </a>The linear throttle potentiometer sensor has no potentiometer adjustments, the following procedure shall thus be applied to
            ensure a correct system operation.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4126"> </a>This procedure must precede the first start-up of the vehicle after replacement of the throttle body, potentiometer, ECU,
         or wiring.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4129"> </a>Make sure that the throttle valve is seated against the stop screw (throttle twistgrip released).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4131"> </a>In this position the ECU learns the position sensor angle. The DDS diagnosis instrument is necessary to carry out this operation.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4134"> </a>The following screens are given just as an example, and thus do not exactly refer to the model described in this manual.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4137"> </a>Select the Ducati model, engine type, and model year.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007604070.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4142"> </a>From the self-diagnosis menu, select the type of engine electronic control unit: OEM or Performance.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007704071.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4147"> </a>Connect the interface wiring to the bike diagnosis socket, and the two VCI interface power clamps to the battery. Connect
            the remaining connector to the VCI (Vehicle Communication Interface) module.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007804072.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4153"> </a>Switch on the instrument panel.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007904073.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4158"> </a>Select the ADJUSTMENTS menu on the left column, then select "TPS Reset", then press ADJUST.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_008004074.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4163"> </a>Press "CONFIRM" and make sure that engine is off, then press "CONFIRM" again.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_008104075.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_008304076.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4170"> </a>Should the engine be ON, a message will ask you to turn it off.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4172"> </a>If the operation has been completed successfully, the corresponding message will be displayed. If not, an error message will
            appear, and the procedure will have to be repeated making sure that the conditions necessary for the TPS reset function to
            be successfully executed are present.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_008304077.jpg"></center>
      </div>
   </body>
